  "Class B, because larger SD means more students scored high": "",
  "Cannot be determined without seeing the raw data": "",
  "They performed equally because the means are the same": "",
  "Both classes have the same center (mean = 78), but Class A's smaller standard deviation (5 vs. 12) means its scores cluster more tightly around 78, indicating more consistent performance.": "",
  "A scientist collected growth data for two plant species over 30 days. Species X has a mean growth of 4.2 cm with IQR of 1.5 cm. Species Y has a mean growth of 4.0 cm with IQR of 5.8 cm. How would you compare these distributions?": "",
